						               													<description>From the instructions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;OBJECT OF THE GAME: To answer opera questions in six categories, then move your token to Valhalla for a chance to win the game.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;My recap: One player rolls the die, moves his pawn and answers the appropriate opera question from a card read by his opponent.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Questions are in the following six categories:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Lives of Opera Composers&amp;#10;Female Singers&amp;#10;Male Singers (and a Few Conductors)&amp;#10;Music, Characters &amp;amp; Plots--Questions about the Opera&amp;#10;Opera Companies&amp;#10;The Media--Recordings, Quotes, Films, Plot Sources&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the question is answered correctly, the player rolls and moves again to another question. If answered incorrectly, play moves to the left.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To win, answer a question correctly in each of six categories, move to Valhalla by exact roll of the die, answer one last question in the category picked by the the opponents.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sounds like Trivial Pursuit for the Opera buff.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contains 6 pawns, one die, score pad, trivia cards, roll-up board and the rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
